709226f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 127th Street
709226f-a.text:
St. Andrew's Protestant Episcopal Church, Fifth Avenue, at N.E. corner
of 127th Street, from near 128th Street.
July 31, 1932.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

715472f-a.title: Manhattan: 127th Street (East) - 5th Avenue
715472f-a.text:
11-15 East 127th Street, adjoining, and east of the N.E. corner of Fifth Avenue. These are three-story frame houses with stucco
fronts.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 275

715474f-a.title: Manhattan: 127th Street (West) - 5th Avenue
715474f-a.text:
5-17 West 127th Street, adjoining, and west of the N.W. corner of Fifth Avenue. No. 7 is a three-story frame house with a brick front and No. 9 is a three-story frame house with a stucco front.
July 28. 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

715475f-a.title: Manhattan: 127th Street (West) - 5th Avenue
715475f-a.text:
9 West 127th Street, north side, west of Fifth avenue. This is a thres-story frame house with a stucco front.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 600
